  "title": "EEGEyeNet Dataset",
  "description": "EEGEyeNet is a simultaneous electroencephalography and eye-tracking dataset designed for eye movement prediction research. This BIDS-standardized version contains data from one subject collected during a controlled experimental paradigm, extracted from the larger EEGEyeNet dataset. The dataset serves as a benchmark for developing and validating computational models of oculomotor behavior using multimodal neurophysiological recordings.",
  "methods_description": "Data were collected simultaneously using electroencephalography (EEG) and eye-tracking technology. The study received ethical approval from the Institutional Review Board of Canton Zurich (BASEC-Nr. 2017-00226).",
